Logistic Regression:  is a supervised machine learning classification algorithm used to predict the probability that an input belongs to a particular class. It is mainly used for binary classification problems, where the output has only two possible classes, such as Yes/No, Pass/Fail, or Spam/Not Spam.

Real-Life Examples
	• Email → Spam or Not Spam 
	• Student → Pass or Fail 
	• Loan → Approved or Rejected 
	• Customer → Buy or Not Buy 
	• Patient → Disease or No Disease
             
